Runner guarantees exercised
----------------------------
Each test-only image ran headlessly under UEFI with `isa-debug-exit`,
`-no-reboot`, a bounded timeout, expected serial marker matching, and the
expected QEMU exit status. `cargo xtask test` rebuilt the normal ISO after the
test-only images. Therefore a timeout, triple fault/reboot, missing marker, or
host-only success would fail the command rather than become evidence.

